---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { useTranslations, getLocalizedPath } from '../../lib/i18n';

const locale = 'en';
const t = useTranslations(locale);
---

<BaseLayout title={`Privacy & Cookies | I Meccanici Rimini`} description="Privacy and cookie policy for I Meccanici Rimini SNC." locale={locale}>
  <section class="pt-24 pb-16">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl">
      <nav class="mb-8" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href={getLocalizedPath('/', locale)} class="text-sm text-[--color-accent] hover:underline">
          &larr; Back to homepage
        </a>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-[--color-primary]">Privacy & Cookie Policy</h1>

      <article class="prose prose-gray max-w-none space-y-8 text-[--color-text-light] leading-relaxed">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[--color-primary] mb-3">1. Data Controller</h2>
          <p>
            The Data Controller is <strong>I MECCANICI RIMINI SNC di Mazzocchi Gianluca e Vicinanza Verter</strong>,
            headquartered at Via Bufalini 18/A, 47921 Rimini, VAT 04 309 360 404.
          </p>
          <p>
            For any requests regarding personal data processing, you may contact the Data Controller
            at <a href="mailto:info@imeccanicirimini.it" class="text-[--color-accent] hover:underline">info@imeccanicirimini.it</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[--color-primary] mb-3">2. Purpose of Data Processing</h2>
          <p>Personal data collected is processed for the following purposes:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-2">
            <li>
              <strong>Responding to contact requests:</strong> data provided through the contact form (name, email, phone, message)
              will be used solely to respond to the requests received.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Newsletter:</strong> if the user subscribes to the newsletter, their email address will be used
              to send commercial communications related to products and services offered.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[--color-primary] mb-3">3. Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
          <p>
            Data processing is based on the data subject's consent (Art. 6(1)(a) of the GDPR) and,
            for contact requests, on the performance of pre-contractual measures taken at the data subject's request
            (Art. 6(1)(b) of the GDPR).
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[--color-primary] mb-3">4. Cookie Policy</h2>
          <p>
            This website uses various types of cookies. A detailed description follows.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-[--color-primary] mt-6 mb-2">Technical Cookies</h3>
          <p>
            Technical cookies are necessary for the proper functioning of the website. They do not require user consent
            as they are strictly necessary to provide the requested service.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-[--color-primary] mt-6 mb-2">Third-Party Cookies – Google Analytics</h3>
          <p>
            This website uses Google Analytics, a web analytics service provided by Google Inc. ("Google").
            Google Analytics uses cookies to help the website analyse how users use the site. The information generated
            by the cookie about website usage (including anonymised IP address) will be transmitted to and stored
            on Google's servers in the United States.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Google will use this information to track and examine website usage, compile reports on website activity
            for website operators, and provide other services related to website activity and Internet usage.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Users can choose to disable Google Analytics by installing the
            <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" class="text-[--color-accent] hover:underline" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Google Analytics opt-out browser add-on</a>.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-[--color-primary] mt-6 mb-2">Third-Party Cookies – Social Media</h3>
          <p>
            Website pages may contain social network plugins (Facebook, Instagram). These plugins may collect
            user browsing data even if the user does not interact with them directly. We recommend consulting
            the privacy policies of the respective social networks:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
            <li>
              <a href="https://www.facebook.com/privacy/explanation" class="text-[--color-accent] hover:underline" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Facebook – Privacy Policy</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="https://help.instagram.com/519522125107875" class="text-[--color-accent] hover:underline" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Instagram – Privacy Policy</a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[--color-primary] mb-3">5. Data Subject Rights</h2>
          <p>
            In accordance with EU Regulation 2016/679 (GDPR), the data subject has the right to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Access</strong> (Art. 15): obtain confirmation as to whether personal data is being processed.</li>
            <li><strong>Rectification</strong> (Art. 16): obtain the correction of inaccurate personal data.</li>
            <li><strong>Erasure</strong> (Art. 17): obtain the deletion of personal data ("right to be forgotten").</li>
            <li><strong>Portability</strong> (Art. 20): receive personal data in a structured, commonly used, machine-readable format.</li>
            <li><strong>Objection</strong> (Art. 21): object to the processing of personal data.</li>
            <li><strong>Withdraw consent</strong>: withdraw consent at any time without affecting the lawfulness of processing based on consent before its withdrawal.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4">
            To exercise their rights, the data subject may contact the Data Controller at
            <a href="mailto:info@imeccanicirimini.it" class="text-[--color-accent] hover:underline">info@imeccanicirimini.it</a>.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            The data subject also has the right to lodge a complaint with the Italian Data Protection Authority
            (<a href="https://www.garanteprivacy.it" class="text-[--color-accent] hover:underline" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">www.garanteprivacy.it</a>).
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[--color-primary] mb-3">6. Data Retention</h2>
          <p>
            Personal data will be retained for the period strictly necessary to fulfil the purposes
            for which it was collected, and in any case in compliance with legal requirements.
          </p>
        </section>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
